Yellowstone Avenue (background, not shown) adjoining the S.W. corner of Darmouth Street (right, partially seen), showing the Abraham Boerum house in the rear of the Abraham Furman house. One Miller was the owner in 1896. The house was razed by fire in 1923.

1922

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

Yellowstone Boulevard (formerly white Pot Road), east side, between Dartmouth and Clyde Streets, showing in 4 views the Abraham Furman farmhouse. The homestead of Caspar Springstein, who settled here about 1700 was opposite the Furman property on the west side of the Boulevard. The buildings seen on the west side of White Pot Road at about Burns Street are no longer in existent in 1925. They were the property of David Springstein in 1909. See other views.

Yellowstone Boulevard at the S.E. corner of Dartmouth Street, showing two views of the Abraham Furman house erected about 1680. Some have it that it was erected about 1700. It was demolished in 1935.
